BY TAKING YOUR EYE
OFF THIS SHOE...

01:31.359 --> 01:34.462
- AND PUTTING IT ON THIS FACE.

01:37.531 --> 01:42.170
- YEAH, BUT THE TROUBLE IS THAT
WE'RE NOT SELLING THIS FACE.

01:42.203 --> 01:45.639
WE'RE SELLING
THIS HIDEOUS SHOE.

01:47.541 --> 01:50.144
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

01:50.178 --> 01:52.313
- UH, I LIKE IT.
IT'S, UM--

01:52.346 --> 01:54.848
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

01:54.882 --> 01:55.883
ONLY...

01:55.916 --> 01:57.718
both: ONLY?

01:57.751 --> 02:03.191
- WELL, WHY TRY AND HIDE
WHAT THE PRODUCT IS?

02:03.224 --> 02:05.659
- GO ON.

02:05.693 --> 02:07.828
- I'D JUST PHOTOGRAPH
THE SHOE

02:07.861 --> 02:11.332
WITH MAYBE
A THOUGHT BUBBLE

02:11.365 --> 02:13.934
SAYING SOMETHING LIKE,

02:13.967 --> 02:17.137
"I'M NOT HIP.
I'M A CLASSIC."

02:19.673 --> 02:21.475
- BRIAN, MAY WE CONTINUE,
PLEASE?

02:21.509 --> 02:24.245
- NO, YOU MAY NOT.

02:24.278 --> 02:26.480
"I'M NOT HIP.
I'M A CLASSIC."

02:26.514 --> 02:30.584
YOU'VE GIVEN IT
PERSONALITY WITH HUMOR

02:30.618 --> 02:34.422
AND RETAINED
ITS SO-CALLED DIGNITY.

02:34.455 --> 02:35.489
HOW LONG HAVE
YOU BEEN HERE?

02:35.523 --> 02:37.658
- TWO MONTHS.

02:37.691 --> 02:40.661
- YOU KNOW, THEY'VE BEEN
WORKING HERE FOR TWO YEARS.

02:40.694 --> 02:42.196
DRAW IT UP.

02:42.230 --> 02:43.497
- ME?

02:43.531 --> 02:44.665
- HIM?
- HIM?

02:44.698 --> 02:47.668
- HIM.

02:47.701 --> 02:49.670
THE BOYS'LL HELP YOU OUT.

02:49.703 --> 02:53.241
WON'T YOU, BOYS?

02:57.878 --> 02:58.846
[both chuckling]

02:58.879 --> 03:01.649
- YOU KNOW, I JUST HAVE TO SAY
THAT A YEAR AGO

03:01.682 --> 03:03.484
I DON'T THINK ANY OF US
WOULD HAVE DREAMED

03:03.517 --> 03:05.686
THAT WE'D BE SITTING HERE
PREGNANT.

03:05.719 --> 03:08.656
I MEAN, IT'S REALLY HAPPENED.
[woman laughs]

03:08.689 --> 03:12.993
- THANKS TO
TWO TRUE TRAILBLAZING PIONEERS,

03:13.026 --> 03:14.762
MELANIE AND LINDSAY.

03:14.795 --> 03:16.497
- NOW YOU'RE ROLE MODELS.

03:16.530 --> 03:18.332
FOR US ALL.
THANK YOU.

03:18.366 --> 03:20.334
[clapping]

03:20.368 --> 03:21.435
- I WISH THEY'D ALL LEAVE.

03:21.469 --> 03:23.671
- [singsong] SHH, YOU DON'T
WANT THEM TO HEAR YOU.

03:23.704 --> 03:24.472
- I DON'T CARE IF THEY DO.

03:24.505 --> 03:25.806
WHY DID WE GO THROUGH
WITH THIS?

03:25.839 --> 03:27.308
- WE PLANNED IT FOR MONTHS.

03:27.341 --> 03:28.876
WE COULDN'T DISAPPOINT
FRANNY AND ZOE,

03:28.909 --> 03:30.244
HOW WOULD THEY FEEL?

03:30.278 --> 03:31.345
- HOW DO YOU THINK I FEEL?

03:31.379 --> 03:33.447
LIKE A LIAR AND A FOOL.

03:33.481 --> 03:34.315
- CAN WE TALK ABOUT THIS LATER?

03:34.348 --> 03:35.849
- SURE, HONEY,
LIKE EVERYTHING ELSE.

03:35.883 --> 03:37.551
I'M GOING TO GO SPIKE
THE PUNCH.

03:37.585 --> 03:38.686
[sighs]

03:38.719 --> 03:39.820
[woman giggles]

03:39.853 --> 03:42.323
- IT'S SO CUTE.

03:43.724 --> 03:46.460
- [sighs]
FRANNY'S SO CUTE AND TINY.

03:46.494 --> 03:48.329
CHRIST,
I HATE CUTE AND TINY.

03:48.362 --> 03:50.964
- [laughs]

03:50.998 --> 03:52.733
- OH, GOD.

03:52.766 --> 03:55.469
YOU'RE PROBABLY
HER BEST FRIEND.

03:55.503 --> 03:58.005
- SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.
- OH, FUCK.

03:58.038 --> 04:00.808
- I'LL DRINK TO THAT.
- [laughs]

04:00.841 --> 04:01.875
- DON'T WORRY ANYWAYS.

04:01.909 --> 04:04.044
I HATE CUTE AND TINY TOO.

04:04.077 --> 04:06.814
- BABY LEATHER JACKET.
AH!

04:06.847 --> 04:09.483
- THAT IS SO ADORABLE!

04:09.517 --> 04:12.486
- OH, CHRIST,
I WOULD JUST KILL

04:12.520 --> 04:13.687
FOR A CIGARETTE RIGHT
ABOUT NOW.

04:13.721 --> 04:14.922
- MM.

04:14.955 --> 04:18.359
- ALL THIS BABY BUSINESS IS
JUST MAKING ME A LITTLE CRAZY.

04:18.392 --> 04:19.860
- WHY,
BECAUSE YOU WANT ONE?

04:19.893 --> 04:22.596
- BECAUSE I DON'T WANT ONE.

04:22.630 --> 04:25.733
DON'T GET ME WRONG,
I LIKE KIDS.

04:25.766 --> 04:27.568
OTHER PEOPLE'S KIDS.

04:27.601 --> 04:30.304
